find 3 sticks between 3 and 6 feet long.  
drill holes in each end. 
tie one end of all three together so they can form a tripod. 
Place that tripod on a sandy beach where each bottom is held in place by the sand.  
In denver, do this on the East side of the South Platte River underneath the 15th street bridge.

